    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors achieved their required levels for MRL 2. The six non-assessed factors are acceptable at required level 1 per ASME V&V 40 MRL 2 guidelines for Class II devices. The output comparison factor is satisfied by CFD parametric sweep results showing RH < 1 across all five operating points. The assessment team accepted the simulation-based evidence as providing sufficient inferential confidence, noting the high mesh quality and validated turbulence closure. The governing requirement REQ-OC-01 specifying experimental-validation as the required verification method was not formally substituted; the activity type employed remains numerical-simulation, creating a latent inference method mismatch that is not surfaced in the summary decision narrative.",
